  "prompt": "Can you have sex, have a period, and still be pregnant?",
  "response": "Yes, it is possible to be pregnant and still experience bleeding that might resemble a period, although it is not a true menstrual period. This can occur for various reasons, such as implantation bleeding, hormonal changes, or other factors. It\u2019s important to note that any bleeding during pregnancy should be discussed with a healthcare provider to ensure that everything is progressing normally.\n\nAdditionally, having sex during pregnancy is generally safe unless advised otherwise by a healthcare provider. If you suspect you are pregnant and are experiencing bleeding, it is crucial to seek medical advice to determine the cause and ensure the health of both the mother and the developing baby.",
